  "text": "Colloquium participants recognized the need for greater transparency in the reporting of scientific data in any and all efforts to improve reproducibility. Without access to data, it is virtually impossible to evaluate reproducibility and possible causes or explanations for any lack of reproducibility. It was recently reported that only 13% of authors with scientific articles published in 2014 made their data freely accessible to others [CITATION_1] . Colloquium participants agreed that data generated by experiments should be accessible outside the research group conducting the experiments.",
